As some of you MAY know, if you play neopets, I created a Splat-A-Sloth script a long time ago, and back then it was able to max out the score, and obtain a gold trophy almost every time. Something's changed since then, and now my script (see below) will hit around 460 points (out of a maximum 500) every single time. 460 is the maximum that it hits once I reduce the wait function to nothing, so it can't possibly be the wait function (I think... unless there's a secret negative wait function :P).

For those unfamiliar with the game that would like to help, it's basically a reflex game. You see the green thing fly out of a tube, and hit spacebar. This script sees it WAY faster than my hands and eyes can react to it, however it ALWAYS maxes out at 460. If there's any way I can make SCAR send the space bar keystroke faster, or just process the entire script faster, it would be GREATLY appreciated. THANKS :D Here's the script

[code]/////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//                  Splat-A-Slot                   //
//              By: Kyrndao and 413X               //
//                                                 //
//      1. Open game in 800 by 600 resolution      //
//      2. Specify game client                     //
//      3. Run the script and with it OWN          //
//                                                 //
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////
program SplatASloth;
var x,y:integer;
begin
clickmouse(318, 328, true);
wait(6200);
repeat
wait(1);
until(findcolortolerance(x,y,39168,162,41,238,55,35));
wait(0); // Change if the paper hits too early.
keydown(32);
wait(20);
keyup(32);
writeln(' Owned!')
end.[/code]



